Most families look forward to exchanging gifts with their loved ones on the day. This year has proven to be a challenging one for many people across the globe. The Covid-19 pandemic saw workers laid off and many companies closing their doors after movement was restricted.  The biggest effect of this was on the earning potential of many who were left jobless. As a result, the tradition of exchanging gifts this Christmas will be that much harder for many. However, a great idea is to make handcrafted gifts that can be treasured for years to come.  Below are ten DIY gifts that loved ones will hold dear:      This list contains a number of items that will last for years to come and evoke memories of a loved one that took the time to make a thoughtful gift as the world battled Covid-19 . 